alternative_parents.description: Organic salt compounds containing a metalloid atom in its ionic form.
alternative_parents.name: Organic metalloid salts

alternative_parents.description: Organoboron compounds where the boron atom is substituted by only two alkyl groups.
alternative_parents.name: Dialkylboranes

alternative_parents.description: Organic compounds containing a bond between a carbon atom and an oxygen atom.
alternative_parents.name: Organooxygen compounds

alternative_parents.description: Derivatives of hydrocarbons obtained by substituting one or more carbon atoms by an heteroatom. They contain at least one carbon atom and heteroatom.
alternative_parents.name: Hydrocarbon derivatives

class.description: Compounds comprising any derivative of the boronic acid functional group, with the general structure RB(OR'')R' (R,R'=organyl; R''=H atom or Organyl group).
class.name: Borinic acid derivatives

description: This compound belongs to the class of organic compounds known as borinic acid esters. These are compounds comprising the boronic acid ester functional group RB(R')OR'' (R,R',R''=organyl; X= any O,N,Hal residue).

direct_parent.description: Compounds comprising the boronic acid ester functional group RB(R')OR'' (R,R',R''=organyl; X= any O,N,Hal residue).
direct_parent.name: Borinic acid esters

kingdom.description: Compounds that contain at least one carbon atom, excluding isocyanide/cyanide and their non-hydrocarbyl derivatives, thiophosgene, carbon diselenide, carbon monosulfide, carbon disulfide, carbon subsulfide, carbon monoxide, carbon dioxide, Carbon suboxide, and dicarbon monoxide.
kingdom.name: Organic compounds

subclass.description: Compounds comprising the boronic acid ester functional group RB(R')OR'' (R,R',R''=organyl; X= any O,N,Hal residue).
subclass.name: Borinic acid esters

superclass.description: Compounds an organic acid or a derivative thereof.
superclass.name: Organic acids and derivatives
